 MARIANHILL SAPS are appealing to members of the community for assistance with regards to the whereabouts of Nkululeko Mpehle (41) from Matatiele in the Eastern Cape. Mpehle was reported missing after he was last seen on March 2, at 10 am in the Tshelimnyama area in Marianhill, where he stays with his brother. He was last seen wearing a long-sleeve shirt with stripes, long brown trouser and black boots. SAPS spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbhele said Mpehle is mentally disturbed. Mbhele appealed to anyone with information to contact Warrant Officer J.B. Sthele at 073 190 1442 or 031 717 2090/1, or the crime stop number 08600 10111.                         â€” Supplied.     24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  